BWT implementation based on http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007%2F978-3-319-02432-5_5

creating the genome data:
-download hg19.2bit from http://genome.ucsc.edu/
-convert it to .fa format with twoBitToFa: ./twoBitToFa hg19.2bit hg19.fa
-remove all characters except A, T, C, G and N, and then pick first Gb: tr -cd 'ATCGN' < hg19.fa | head -c 1000000000 > genome1

compiling:

mingw on windows:
g++ src/bwt.cpp src/main.cpp -std=c++11 -Wall -static -static-libgcc -static-libstdc++

ubuntu 13.10 with gcc 4.8.1:
g++ src/bwt.cpp src/main.cpp -std=c++11 -Wall
